main event: An instructor pilot observed sausage-shaped vapor trails at very high altitude over Goose Air Base, Labrador.
interesting points: The vapor trails were reported to form in a serpentine pattern at an altitude of 43,000 feet., The vapor trails were seen during a flight by MATS instructor pilot and confirmed by another pilot., The sighting was reported to tower operations but no other aircraft were known to be in the area., The source had prior experience with vapor trails from his time in Europe during World War II., The report concluded there was insufficient data for evaluation.
witness description: MATS instructor pilot and a major
